iv class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><a id="about"></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="0c7894d6-4fb5-f12b-9476-7572b78c5384" class="widget"><style>[data-widget-id="0c7894d6-4fb5-f12b-9476-7572b78c5384"]{text-align:center}.leadbox img[src$="image_placeholder.svg"]{max-height:29px}</style><img class="lp-image" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/k_zecv0d_zJVuiPq5nyvbQGxexYXIut-Fkr6CuJhSPV9TzPrk2C-kWPa5s7IndVoxZQ98VC0hyHvwXN7U9TSDQ=s0" alt="" style="max-width: 400px;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="c7eb931b-e161-822e-315d-a53f68b22798" class="widget"><div class="lp-text" style="min-height:20px;outline:0" spellcheck="false"><p class="line-height-scale-3 font-scale-4 text-align-center"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong><span style="font-family: Montserrat;"><span class="font-scale-10">COURSE DESCRIPTION</span></span><span style="font-family: Roboto;"><span class="font-scale-5">&nbsp;</span></span></strong></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="555566c9-3a43-f1c2-5676-7b39af498e15" class="widget"><div class="lp-text" style="min-height:20px;outline:0" spellcheck="false"><p class="line-height-scale-4 font-scale-4 text-align-center"><span class="font-scale-6">This fun, dynamic, and fully interactive 18-hour online course will prepare you to take your peer support skills to the next level in resilience and whole health. During the live skill-based class sessions, you’ll get the chance to interact with your facilitator and fellow classmates in an exciting virtual classroom. You’ll also be paired one on one with a learning partner to optimize your learning experience during the course. So get ready to expand your skills in updated peer support competency areas for the 21st Century in recovery and resilience services, group facilitation, whole health integration, trauma informed care, addiction recovery, and much more.</span>&nbsp;</p><p class="line-height-scale-3 font-scale-4 text-align-left"><span class="font-scale-3"><em>Note: A certificate will be awarded by your Masters and/or PhD level facilitator(s) for successful course completion. The certificate may count toward CEU’s based upon the authorization of your licensing entity.</em></span>&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="column flex__item--md-1 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="f6b37521-f457-77a4-3118-48e9d5047009"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="aa6c8102-2e36-f977-0d12-2b73c6fb990d" class="widget"><div class="lp-space"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="53e10821-5e19-82e7-a9ed-e42603e40f61" class="widget"><div class="lp-space"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="section" data-guid="c424a17f-40e8-93d4-8331-d3ed068fe8fd" style="border-color: rgb(194, 194, 194); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgb(194, 194, 194);"><div class="container"><div class="layout flex flex--12"><div class="column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="b0ace2c5-2705-e679-0406-b24f53fec05e"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><a id="instructor"></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="layout flex flex--12"><div class="column flex__item--md-7 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="8482448c-0534-d6d4-4676-958961e20139"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="05568cd3-0cda-194e-dd55-63c298ba1bda" class="widget"><style>[data-widget-id="05568cd3-0cda-194e-dd55-63c298ba1bda"]{text-align:center}.leadbox img[src$="image_placeholder.svg"]{max-height:29px}</style><img class="lp-image" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/U-l4xGtr-a6mQB1NyLytzyW-bY91VM7N2I784dl88U_4QfJXjZNG1On2h50m1N1uKaOOI96BZhWR6_x36tbGzA=s0" alt="" style="max-width: 515px;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="column flex__item--md-5 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="54f7670b-55a1-f3d4-48a1-5d1f72817531"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="81e47796-1156-977c-e106-576f4027d643" class="widget"><div class="lp-headline" spellcheck="false"><h2 class="line-height-scale-5 font-scale-6 text-align-left lp-headline subhead"><span style="font-family: Montserrat;"><strong>COURSE INSTRUCTOR</strong></span></h2></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="c2ac86ae-12f4-a514-e7c9-67860735f6d6" class="widget"><div class="lp-text" style="min-height:20px;outline:0" spellcheck="false"><p class="line-height-scale-3 font-scale-4 text-align-left"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-family: Roboto;"><span class="font-scale-7"><strong>Chris Martin</strong>, MA in Education and Education Counseling, ITE</span></span></span></p><p class="line-height-scale-4 font-scale-4 text-align-left"><span class="font-scale-3">Chris has a personal experience of recovery from mental illness and strengthened resilience. He has over 25 years of experience as an adult educator and curriculum designer which enables him to customize the design, development, writing, and delivery of learning programs in a way to optimize learning and skill transfer. In addition to public school teaching and corporate training, Chris has spent the last 15 years in the field of mental health. In 2002, he collaborated with Dr. Lori Ashcraft to develop the very first Associate Degree in Recovery program in partnership with South Mountain Community College.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="line-height-scale-4 font-scale-4 text-align-left"><span class="font-scale-3">Chris is also the author and/or co-author of numerous training materials, workbooks, and workshops. He has delivered recovery and resilience based training to mental health professionals all over the United States, including New Zealand, Canada, Singapore, and the United Kingdom. Chris says his greatest accomplishments in life are his five children and seven grandchildren.&nbsp;</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="layout flex flex--12"><div class="column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="f38ac63f-6339-34d4-f704-288f121ec48b"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"></div></div></div></div></section><section class="section" data-guid="60227b67-0f37-8072-142b-51ad72d8e457" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="container"><div class="layout flex flex--12"><div class="column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12" data-guid="8e75698d-1a4a-eda3-5825-017425e63434"><div class="inner-column" style="border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-image: url(&quot;&quot;); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><a id="schedule"></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row flex flex--12"><div class="composite flex__item--md-6 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="widget-row flex flex--12"><div class="flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12 widget-widget"><div data-widget-id="40fd1901-afe8-0099-f439-989490826a6d" class="widget"><div class="lp-text" style="min-height:20px;outline:0" spellcheck="false"><p class="line-height-scale-3 font-scale-4 text-align-center"><span style="font-family: Montserrat;"><span class="font-scale-10"><strong>COURSE OUTLINE</strong></span></span>&nbsp;</p><p class="line-height-scale-3 font-scale-4 text-align-left">The interactive, online course will be delivered in 2 two-hour sessions per week for 4 consecutive weeks plus an additional ninth 2-hour session to complete your practical and prepare for your final exam. Course work includes a mid-term quiz, 7 home-work assignments, class exercises, a competency based practical and final exam. All class sessions will be recorded to provide for make-up sessions. Student(s) can miss no more than two class sessions in this accelerated course. If a student misses one or two class session(s), he or she will need to attend the recorded make-up session for the session(s) missed.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="composite flex__item--md-6 flex__item--xs-12"><div class="inner-composite flex flex--12 undefined"><div class="widget-column flex__item--md-12 flex__item--xs-12"><div class=